  "text": "The `acks` configuration propagates through four distinct stages in the Kafka codebase:\n\n**Stage 1 \u2013 Definition (ProducerConfig.java):** The constant `ACKS_CONFIG = \"acks\"` is declared at line 123. The ConfigDef static initializer (line 383) registers it as a STRING type with allowed values `\"all\"`, `\"-1\"`, `\"0\"`, `\"1\"` and default `\"all\"`. The method `parseAcks()` (line 639) normalizes the string `\"all\"` to `\"-1\"`. The method `postProcessAndValidateIdempotenceConfigs()` (line 577) calls `parseAcks()` and validates that `acks` must be `\"all\"` (i.e., `-1`) when idempotence is enabled.\n\n**Stage 2 \u2013 Producer Initialization (KafkaProducer.java):** In `newSender()` (line 526), the config value is read via `producerConfig.getString(ProducerConfig.ACKS_CONFIG)`, parsed to a `short`, and passed directly as a constructor argument to the `Sender` instance.\n\n**Stage 3 \u2013 Protocol Encoding (Sender.java \u2192 ProduceRequest.java):** The `Sender` class stores `acks` as a `private final short` field (line 99). In `sendProduceRequests()` (line 856) \u2192 `sendProduceRequest()` (line 864), `acks` is embedded into the `ProduceRequestData` via `.setAcks(acks)` (line 899) and passed to `ProduceRequest.builder()`. The `ProduceRequest` class (and its inner `Builder`) stores and exposes the `acks` field \u2014 it is serialized into the produce request wire protocol. The `acks` value also controls whether a response is expected at all (`acks != 0` at line 912).\n\n**Stage 4 \u2013 Broker-Side Ack Behavior (KafkaApis.scala \u2192 ReplicaManager.scala \u2192 Partition.scala):** `KafkaApis.handleProduceRequest()` reads `produceRequest.acks` to skip request throttling when `acks == 0` and to decide whether to send a response immediately or asynchronously. It passes `requiredAcks = produceRequest.acks` to `ReplicaManager.handleProduceAppend()`. The ReplicaManager validates the value in `isValidRequiredAcks()` (only -1, 0, 1 are valid), routes through `appendRecords()` \u2192 `appendRecordsToLeader()` \u2192 `appendToLocalLog()` which calls `Partition.appendRecordsToLeader()`. The `delayedProduceRequestRequired()` method (line 1355) checks `requiredAcks == -1` to determine whether to wait for follower replication via a DelayedProduce purgatory, or acknowledge immediately.",
